<h1>Scientific interests</h1>
<ul>
<li>
Development and application of QM/MM methods. In particular for
modelling photochemical processes in large condensed phase systems,
such as proteins and solvated chromophores.
</li>
</ul>

<h1>Computing experience</h1>
<ul>
<li>Programming experience in C and Fortran77. Implemented a <a
HREF="http://md.chem.rug.nl/~groenhof/qmmm.html">QM/MM interface</a>
in the <a HREF="www.gromacs.org">Gromacs</a> molecular dynamics
program. Also experience in modifying existing quantum chemistry
codes, such as Gaussian, GAMESS-UK, and MOPAC. Broad experience on
different UNIX systems (linux, MacOS X, AIX, Irix), both at the
administrator and user level, including set-up and maintenance of
<a HREF=http://www.beowulf.org/>beowulf clusters</a>. 
</li>
</ul>

